com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.component.model

Class WebCmsComponentModelSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.component.model.WebCmsComponentModelSet

  • public class WebCmsComponentModelSet
extends Object
    Represents a lookup for WebCmsComponentModels that are accessible by name. All components in a single set are expected to be owned by the value getOwner().

    A set can have a fetcher function value (setFetcherFunction(BiFunction)). This function will be used to retrieve a component if it is not yet present in the set. A component name will only ever be looked up once unless it is removed again.

    Since:
    0.0.2
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public void add(WebCmsComponentModel componentModel)
        Add a component to the ordered list. If another component with that name exists, it will be replaced by name but will still be added to the ordered collection.
        Parameters:
        componentModel - to add

      • put

        public void put(@NonNull
                @NonNull String name,
                WebCmsComponentModel componentModel)
        Register a component under a specific name in the set. The actual value of WebCmsComponentModel.getName() will be ignored.

        If the model is null, you are explicitly marking a component as unavailable. In case of a fetcher function it will not be looked up either.

        Parameters:
        name - to register the component under
        componentModel - to add

      • contains

      • get

        public WebCmsComponentModel get(String name)
        Gets the component with that name. If a fetcherFunction has been specified, it will be used to retrieve the component if it is not yet present.
        Returns:
        component or null if not found

      • remove

        public WebCmsComponentModel remove(String name)
        Removes the component registered with that name. Note that if a fetcher function is set, the component will be fetched again. If you do not want this, set the component for that name explicitly to null.
        Parameters:
        name - of the component to remove
        Returns:
        component removed

      • remove

        public boolean remove(@NonNull
                      @NonNull WebCmsComponentModel componentModel)
        Removes the component model. If the same component model were to be registered under multiple names, all of them would be removed.
        Parameters:
        componentModel - to remove
        Returns:
        true if at least one entry has been removed
